<TITLE> Henry continues recovery from knee injury </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BARCELONA, May 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Thierry Henry joined the rest of the Barcelona squad for their pre-training warm up on Friday as he continues his recovery from a knee injury, the club said on their website (www.fcbarcelona.cat). The striker then worked apart from the rest of the group as he bids to be fit for Wednesday's Champions League final against Manchester United, the club said, adding that midfielder Andres Iniesta, who is recuperating from a thigh strain, did some light training on his own at the Nou Camp. Coach Pep Guardiola told a news conference later on Friday he had spoken to midfielder Seydou Keita about possibly playing at left back to fill in for the suspended Eric Abidal. "He said he was prepared to play anywhere if it would help the team but pointed out the risk seeing as he has never played there before," Guardiola said. "This helps me and I have four days to decide what I will 
